HEADWORD: Ant-lion
<hw>Ant"-li`on</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A neuropterous insect, the larva of which makes in the sand a
pitfall to capture ants, etc. The common American species is
<spn>Myrmeleon obsoletus</spn>, the European is <spn>Myrmeleon
formicarius</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antoecians</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Antoeci</ent>⟦br⟧
